#: input:6094 input:6107 input:6120 input:6145 input:6169 input:6194 input:6218
#: input:6242 input:6263 input:6286 input:6296 input:6305 input:6314 input:6323
#: input:6332 input:6341 standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"If you’re low on soldiers to occupy new military sites, use the downward "
"arrow button to decrease the capacity. You can also click on a soldier to "
"send him away."
msgstr ""
"Si disposeu de pocs soldats per ocupar els edificis militars nous, cliqueu "
"la fletxa descendent per reduir el nombre de soldats desitjats. També podeu "
"clicar un soldat per fer-lo sortir de l'edifici."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: Guardhouse
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:5980 input:5980
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"Hey soldier, even if this is the smallest of our military buildings you "
"still must not sleep all day!"
msgstr ""
"Hola soldat, encara que aquest sigui el més petit dels nostres edificis "
"militars, encara no has de dormir tot el dia!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: Guardhouse
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:5982 input:5982
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Officer visiting a remote guardhouse"
msgstr "Oficial visitant un cos de guàrdia remot"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: Guardhall
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:5993 input:5993
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "In this hall we praise the fight, Satul will warm us day and night."
msgstr "En aquesta sala lloem la lluita, Satul ens escalfarà dia i nit."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: Guardhall
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:5995 input:5995
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Scribbling on the wall of a guardhall"
msgstr "Gargots a la paret d'una sala de guàrdia"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: Small Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6006 input:6006
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"With three soldiers we can achieve an optimal balance between military power "
"and building cost."
msgstr ""
"Amb tres soldats podem aconseguir un equilibri òptim entre la potència "
"militar i el cost de construcció."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: Small Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6008 input:6008
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Notes on the building instructions"
msgstr "Notes sobre les instruccions de construcció"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6020 input:6020
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"All the other tribes envy us for our towers, elegant outside, comfortable "
"inside, still perfect for defense."
msgstr ""
"Totes les altres tribus ens envegen per les nostres torres, elegants per "
"fora, còmodes per dins, encara perfectes per a la defensa."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6022 input:6022
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Soldier handing over his duties to a younger one"
msgstr "Soldat cedint els seus deures a un més jove"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: High Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6035 input:6035
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"Beware our mighty high towers! From the topmost spot we can see wide into "
"the lands and spot the enemy far away."
msgstr ""
"Compte amb les nostres poderoses torres altes! Des del punt més alt podem "
"veure amples les terres i veure l'enemic lluny."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: High Tower
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6038 input:6038
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Soldier showing off a High Tower"
msgstr "Soldat mostrant una Torre Alta"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for an Europeans production site: Castle
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6051 input:6051
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"Sometimes even we Atlanteans need to use brute force, but we always play it "
"wisely."
msgstr ""
"De vegades, fins i tot els atlants necessitem utilitzar la força bruta, però "
"sempre hi juguem amb prudència."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for an Europeans production site: Castle
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6053 input:6053
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "‘Wisdom of the Fight’ by the warriors’ guild"
msgstr "‘La saviesa de la lluita’ del gremi de guerrers"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6061 input:6061
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"‘The log cabin was so small that two men could hardly live there. But we "
"were young and carefree. We just relished our freedom and the responsibility "
"as an outpost.’"
msgstr ""
"'La cabana de troncs era tan petita que gairebé dos homes hi podien viure. "
"Però érem joves i despreocupats. Només vam gaudir de la nostra llibertat i "
"la responsabilitat com a avançada."

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Barbarian military site: Sentry
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6063 input:6063
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid "Boldreth,<br>about his time as young soldier"
msgstr "Boldreth,<br>sobre el seu temps com a jove soldat"

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore helptext for a Barbarian military site: Barrier
#: addons/europeans_all.wad/tribes/initialization/units.lua:6074 input:6074
#: standard
msgctxt "europeans_building"
msgid ""
"‘When we looked down to the valley from our newly established barrier, we "
"felt that the spirit of our fathers was with us.’"
msgstr ""
"\"Quan vam mirar a la vall des de la nostra barrera acabada d'establir, vam "
"sentir que l'esperit dels nostres pares estava amb nosaltres\"."

